CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Votes for Guess Who? - Fifth Ward Alderman Harry B. Fitzgerald, left, was snapped on Tuesday, as he asked and answered a question put to Atty. K. Leroy Irvis and his wife, Kathryn, center, as the couple voted in Fifth Ward's 15th District. Mrs. Cora B. Rodgers, right, candidate for re-election as committeewoman in the district, looks on.  Mr. Irvis won nomination for the State Legislature in the First Legislative District in Tuesday's final count. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alderman Harry B. Fitzgerald talking to Atty. K. Leroy Irvis, Kathryn Irvis, and Cora B. Rodgers, in Fifth Ward polling place
